Audit Trail Q&A System for Internal Finance Teams
One-line Pitch: An AI-assisted audit support system that scans ledger entries, detects anomalies using deterministic rules, retrieves relevant accounting policies and similar historical audit cases using RAG, and drafts explainable audit notes for internal finance teams.
Problem Statement
Internal audit teams manually review thousands of financial transactions to identify duplicate payments, threshold violations, suspicious vendor activity, round-number estimates, debit/credit mismatches, and other anomalies. After identifying issues, auditors must search accounting policies and previous audit reports to determine the appropriate action. This project automates the first-pass audit workflow by combining rule-based anomaly detection with Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) and an MCP server for AI tool calling.
Objectives
• Automate anomaly detection.
• Retrieve applicable accounting policies.
• Retrieve similar resolved audit cases.
• Generate explainable audit notes.
• Provide dashboards, reports, and human review workflow.
Technology Stack
Frontend: React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, React Query
Backend: FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Pydantic, JWT Authentication
Database: PostgreSQL (SQLite for development)
Vector Database: Qdrant (or ChromaDB)
LLM: Claude API
Embeddings: sentence-transformers (BGE or MiniLM)
MCP: MCP Python SDK
Deployment: Docker, Docker Compose
Monitoring: Prometheus, Grafana (optional)
